cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.FL

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a formalisation of pGCL in Isabelle/HOL, which is a logical framework. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as pGCL is a programming language for probabilistic programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the integration with existing automation support and the extension of the model to incorporate existing results. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper motivates the applicability of the formalism to the mechanical verification of probabilistic security properties and side-channel countermeasures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents a formalisation of a programming language.
